THE WORK IS PROVIDED "AS IS" AND "AS AVAILABLE", WITHOUT WARRANTIES OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, TITLE, NON‑INFRINGEMENT, OR ACCURACY. THE LICENSOR DOES NOT WARRANT THAT THE WORK WILL BE UNINTERRUPTED, SECURE, OR ERROR‑FREE.
ARTICLE 12: LIMITATION OF LIABILITY

IN NO EVENT SHALL THE LICENSOR BE LIABLE FOR ANY DIRECT, INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES, INCLUDING LOSS OF PROFITS, GOODWILL, USE, OR DATA, ARISING OUT OF OR RELATING TO THIS COVENANT OR THE WORK, EVEN IF ADVISED OF THE POSSIBILITY OF SUCH DAMAGES. THE LICENSOR’S TOTAL LIABILITY FOR ANY CLAIM SHALL NOT EXCEED $10,000 USD.
ARTICLE 13: INDEMNIFICATION

The Recipient shall indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the Licensor from any claims, damages, or expenses (including reasonable attorneys’ fees) arising from:

    (a) the Recipient’s use or distribution of the Work;

    (b) any Derivative Work created by the Recipient;

    (c) any violation of this Covenant; and

    (d) any claim that the Recipient’s use infringes third‑party rights.

This indemnification does not apply to individuals or entities with Annual Revenue under $100,000 USD.
ARTICLE 14: MODIFICATION OF COVENANT (PROSPECTIVE ONLY)

14.1 Unilateral Amendment for Future Versions.
The Licensor may publish updated versions of this Covenant. Any update applies only to versions of the Work downloaded after the effective date of the update. Recipients who obtained the Work under an earlier version may continue to use that version under the original terms, or choose to upgrade to the new version under the new terms.

14.2 Notice.
The Licensor will update the "Effective Date" and post a summary. Continued use of a newly downloaded version after 30 days constitutes acceptance of the new terms for that version.

14.3 No Retroactive Changes.
No modification of this Covenant shall apply to any use or distribution that occurred before the modification’s effective date.
ARTICLE 15: SEVERABILITY

If any provision of this Covenant is held unenforceable, the remainder shall continue in full force. The unenforceable provision shall be reformed to the minimum extent necessary to make it enforceable. If reformation is impossible, the court shall strike that provision and enforce the rest.
ARTICLE 16: ACCEPTANCE OF TERMS

16.1 Manifestation of Assent.
By downloading, cloning, installing, executing, or distributing the Work, the Recipient affirmatively agrees to be bound by all terms.

16.2 No Browsewrap.
Mere viewing of the Work in a web browser without obtaining a copy does not constitute acceptance.

16.3 AI Scrapers.
Automated crawling or scraping of the Work’s source code without downloading (e.g., for training datasets) is not acceptance of this Covenant and is not governed by its terms; such use is governed solely by copyright law and any applicable platform terms.
ARTICLE 17: GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION

17.1 Governing Law.
This Covenant shall be governed by the laws of the jurisdiction identified as the Licensor’s Primary Place of Business or Habitual Residence in the Copyright Notice. If the Licensor is an individual without a registered business, the governing law is the law of the country of their habitual residence.

17.2 Exclusive Jurisdiction.
Any dispute arising under this Covenant shall be resolved exclusively in the courts of that jurisdiction. The Recipient submits to personal jurisdiction there and waives venue objections.

17.3 Service of Process.
Service of process may be effected by: (a) registered mail to the Recipient’s registered address; (b) email to the address provided by the Recipient; or (c) if no address is available, by public notice in the Work’s repository accompanied by a reasonable attempt to contact through other means.

17.4 Anonymous and Pseudonymous Enforcements.
If the Recipient is anonymous or operates under a pseudonym (including but not limited to online aliases, Discord handles, or GitHub usernames), service of process and legal notice may be validly executed by public announcement in the Work's primary repository, combined with a direct message or issue creation directed at any online platform or service provider hosting the Recipient's products, services, or communication channels (e.g., GitHub, Discord, Tebex, Patreon, or Minecraft Marketplace).

17.5 Sanctions and Force Majeure.
Nothing in this Covenant shall compel the Recipient or Licensor to violate any applicable international trade sanctions, export controls, or local banking regulations. In the event that international sanctions block monetary transfer between the Recipient's and Licensor's jurisdictions, the Recipient must deposit any required fees or revenue share into a local escrow account in the Recipient's jurisdiction, to be held in trust for the Licensor until such transfer becomes legally permissible.

ARTICLE 18: ENTIRE AGREEMENT

This Covenant constitutes the entire agreement between the Licensor and the Recipient concerning the Work. It supersedes all prior communications. Any separate written agreement (e.g., a commercial license) overrides conflicting terms.
ARTICLE 19: USE AS A GENERIC TEMPLATE

19.1 Permission to Use as Template.
Any copyright holder may use this Covenant as a license for their own Work by:

    (a) reproducing the license text verbatim (including this Article 19);

    (b) completing the Copyright Notice header with their own information; and

    (c) not altering the license text below the header.

19.2 Version Control.
Version numbers of this Covenant are controlled solely by Aethelgrad Studio, the original author. Third parties may not publish modified versions under the ARPCC name. However, any copyright holder using the template may state "Licensed under ARPCC v2.2" without implying endorsement.

19.3 No Endorsement.
Use of this Covenant as a template does not imply endorsement by, sponsorship by, or affiliation with Aethelgrad Studio.

